🚖 City Fare Analysis DashboardOverviewCity Fare Analysis is a data-driven project focused on visualizing and interpreting ride-booking data to improve urban mobility services. This repository contains the analysis of over 148,000 bookings made throughout 2024, examining revenue streams, trip distributions, and service quality.🚀 Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)Total Booking Volume: ~148.77K total bookings.Success Rate: 61.97% of total bookings were successfully completed.Cancellation Rate: 25% overall cancellation rate.Average Fare: Maintained at approximately $3.50 per trip.Revenue Leader: UPI is the dominant payment method, contributing $20.3M in booking value.📊 Feature InsightsFare Trends Over Time: Tracks monthly revenue and trip counts from January to December 2024, highlighting peak demand periods.Vehicle Performance: Comparative analysis of vehicle types including Uber XL, Premier, Sedan, eBike, and Auto, measuring total distance and booking frequency.Cancellation Analysis: Detailed breakdown of why trips fail, categorized by both customer reasons (e.g., "Change of plans") and driver reasons (e.g., "Customer related issues").Service Quality: Tracks customer and driver ratings across different vehicle segments to ensure high standards of user experience.🛠️ Tech StackData Visualization: Power BI Analysis Segments: Time-series analysis, Payment gateway distribution, and Distance-based revenue categorization.📂 Project StructureCity_Fare_Dashboard.pbix: The primary interactive dashboard file.Data/: (Optional) Raw or cleaned datasets used for the analysis.Screenshots/: Visual representations of the dashboard pages.📈 Visualizations IncludedFare Type Distribution: Revenue share by vehicle category.Booking Status Summary: Breakdown of completed, cancelled, and incomplete rides.Payment Method Analysis: Distribution of transactions via UPI, Cash, Wallet, and Cards.Distance vs. Revenue: Analysis of "Revenue Per KM" across short, medium, and long-distance categories.
